column1:
[['1.  New moderate pulmonary edema with increased bilateral pleural effusions and cardiomegaly. 2.  Right upper lobe pneumonia.  Recommend followup to resolution. 3.  Stable calcification of the mitral annulus.'
  None]]
column2:
[['1.  Low lung volumes with bibasilar atelectasis. 2.  Endotracheal tube terminates approximately 3 cm above the carina.'
  None]]
column3:
[['1.  Hyperinflation of the lungs. 2.  Right basilar opacity may be due to atelectasis versus consolidation due to infection in the appropriate clinical setting. 3.  Stable biapical pleural thickening.'
